Airlines offer passengers for a few years Wi-Fi if the altitude has been reached.
The adapted to Wi-Fi systems flyers are also less susceptible to interference.
The vast majority of passenger aircraft should be suitable for the greater use of electronic devices according to the new guidelines, Huerta said.
Today's electronic devices emit radio in general much less radiation than previous generations.
E-reader, for example, emit minimal radiation when page is turned.
But when downloading or sending of data transmission values ​​are stronger.
Among the advocates of a relaxation of the limitations of the instruments use by passengers counts Amazon.com.
